$$
\mathrm{Ag}^{+}+\mathrm{Br}^{-} \rightleftharpoons \mathrm{AgBr}
$$
Precipitation starts when ionic product just exceeds solubility product
$$
\begin{aligned}
& \mathrm{K}_{\text {sp }}=\left[\mathrm{Ag}^{+}\right]\left[\mathrm{Br}^{-}\right] \\
& {\left[\mathrm{Br}^{-}\right]=\frac{\mathrm{K}_{\mathrm{sp}}}{\left[\mathrm{Ag}^{+}\right]}=\frac{5 \times 10^{-13}}{0.05}=10^{-11}}
\end{aligned}
$$
i.e., precipitation just starts when $10^{-11}$ moles of $\mathrm{KBr}$ is added to $1 \mathrm{~L}$ of $\mathrm{AgNO}_3$ solution.
No. of moles of $\mathrm{KBr}$ to be added
$$
\begin{aligned}
\therefore \text { weight of } \mathrm{KBr} \text { to be added } & =10^{-11} \times 120 \\
& =1.2 \times 10^{-9} \mathrm{~g}
\end{aligned}
$$

